1 9. Transparency. An electric distribution utility shall file an annual report with the
2 commission detailing:
3 A. The total receivables purchased pursuant to subsection 6;
4 B. Any discount rates applied under subsection 6; and
5 C. Collection performance pursuant to subsection 7, paragraph C.
6 10. Regulation of aggregators. The following provisions apply to aggregators.
7 A. An aggregator shall treat customer data as confidential information that is not
8 subject to public disclosure.
9 B. An aggregator that supplies electricity is considered a competitive electricity
10 provider under section 3203 for the purpose of access to the electric distribution utility's
11 load data and for the purpose of ceasing operations.
12 11. Rulemaking. The commission shall adopt rules for the implementation of this
13 section no later than January 1, 2027, including, but not limited to:
14 A. Standardized customer opt-out procedures;
15 B. Purchase of receivables program design and discount rate methodology; and
16 C. Consumer protection and transparency requirements.
17 Rules adopted pursuant to this subsection are routine technical rules as defined in Title 5,
18 chapter 375, subchapter 2-A.
19 SUMMARY
2200 This bill authorizes municipalities and groups of municipalities to establish community
2211 choice aggregation programs. Under a community choice aggregation program with a plan
2222 approved by the Public Utilities Commission, eligible customers are automatically enrolled
2233 in the community choice aggregation program unless they choose to opt out. The bill
2244 establishes requirements for customer notifications and protections and directs the
2255 commission to adopt rules for community choice aggregation program authorization,
2266 standardized opt-out procedures and consumer safeguards. The bill also requires electric
2277 distribution utilities to implement a purchase of receivables program requiring utilities to
2288 purchase community choice aggregation program receivables at a discount rate approved
2299 by the commission, consolidate billing, assume collection responsibility and report to the
3300 commission annually.
